## Verify the OIDC identity provider (Keycloak)

{{ reason }}

- **Open Keycloak:** http://localhost:{{ env_map['KEYCLOAK_HTTP_PORT'] }}
  (admin console login: `{{ env_map['KEYCLOAK_ADMIN_USER'] }}` / `{{ env_map['KEYCLOAK_ADMIN_PASSWORD'] }}`)
- **Open the gateway UI:** {{ gateway_url }}
  (Config -> Security -> Identity Providers -> `keycloak` -> Test Login)

The `keycloak` provider is pre-seeded as an OpenID Connect IdP wired to the
bundled Keycloak realm. The realm ships a demo user **`demo` / `demo`** with the
`ignition-admin` role. Run **Test Login** on the `keycloak` provider and sign in
as that user; the test panel should return the user's claims (including the
`ignition-admin` realm role). To make Keycloak the gateway login provider, set it
on the relevant security level under Config -> Security.

> **Demo credentials:** the OIDC client secret is a fixed demo value
> (`ignition-oidc-demo-secret`) shipped in both the Keycloak realm and the
> gateway IdP config, exactly like the demo `admin` / `ignition` passwords. The
> Keycloak frontend hostname is pinned to `http://localhost:{{ env_map['KEYCLOAK_HTTP_PORT'] }}`
> so OIDC issuer and redirect URLs stay consistent. For a real deployment,
> rotate the client secret in Keycloak and re-seed it, and front Keycloak with
> HTTPS. If you change `KEYCLOAK_HTTP_PORT` in `.env`, update the
> `authorizationEndpoint` / `endSessionEndpoint` / `providerId` URLs in the
> seeded `identity-provider/keycloak/config.json` to match.
